The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

The little lives lost and ruined

Estimates suggest one-third of the tsunami disaster 

victims in South Asia were children, those youngest and too fragile to defend 

themselves against the giant killer waves. Hundreds of thousands have survived, 

but have either lost parents, relatives, homes or belongings, and face an uncertain 

future. Some are too little to even understand what has hit them and the consequences. 

What happens now...?




